content.html: Cheetahs don't roar, they meow. The Felidae family is subdivided between "roaring cats" and "purring cats". The ability to roar is made possible by a special two-piece hyoid bone in the throat. Cheetahs only have a one-piece hyoid bone [ðŸ“¹ meskal44: buff.ly/2VwrnGl]
